seg.seg:
uerum id ita demum faciunt, si
                                re adhuc integra consulantur ipsi, et probata causa, repetitis ac
                                non redditis rebus, belli autores inferendi sint;

tela sunt eminus sagittae,
                                quas acerrime simul et certissime iaculantur, non pedites modo sed
                                ex equis etiam;

And for this cause they thynke
                                it to cruell an acte to reuenge that losse wyth the death of
                                many;

Therefore they
                                hyere soldyours oute of all countreys, and sende them to battayle;
                                but cheiflye of the Zapoletes.

Their weapons
                                be arrowes afarre of, which they shote both strongely and suerly;
                                not onelye fotemen but also horsemen.
